{"issues":[{"number":36329,"title":"[Compiler Bug]: do not remove comments during compilation","body":"### What kind of issue is this?

- [x] React Compiler core (the JS output is incorrect, or your app works incorrectly after optimization)
- [ ] babel-plugin-react-compiler (build issue installing or using the Babel plugin)
- [ ] eslint-plugin-react-hooks (build issue installing or using the eslint plugin)
- [ ] react-compiler-healthcheck (build issue installing or using the healthcheck script)

### Link to repro

https://playground.react.dev/#N4Igzg9grgTgxgUxALhAgHgBwjALgAgBMEAzAQygBsCSoA7OXASwjvwFkBPAQU0wAoAlPmAAdNvjiswBANoyyuBABp8YBLgDKuRQgC6+ALz4o67bqHj8+APQAqfEzoK6AIyr47Nq-hgbYbAA8hEwAbgB8wApKAL6BNiERANziMeIgyiBSdCRMAOYoIGISNjZSALaYTJSKLHTsEMTI+KIgZJSUrakZ4AAWEADuAJJ0SjB07WAo5JTqMUA

### Repro steps

From https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/32950#issuecomment-4011608396 and the updated playground link, we can see that comments are being removed by the compiler. 

In this case the comment is used by other tools to affect their behaviour so should not be removed by the react-compiler, especially since it&#39;s encouraged to put the `babel-plugin-react-compiler` as the first babel plugin (i.e. run before all others).

### How often does this bug happen?

Every time

### What version of React are you using?

Any

### What version of React Compiler are you using?

